@NODE "PalPatch" "What is PalPatch?"
@TOC "Author"

@{par}                               @{fg shine}What is PalPatch?@{fg text}
@{par}
@{par}PalPatch is another utility which @{"Trevor Morris" LINK "Author"} requested of @{"me" LINK "Author"}. This one
@{par}allows you to substitute the currently active Workbench palette into any
@{par}image(s), pattern(s), brush(es), etc. provided it is an IFF.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Requirements" "System Requirements for PalPatch"

@{par}                       @{fg shine}System Requirements for PalPatch@{fg text}
@{par}
@{par}                           Requires 2.X and higher.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Usage" "How to use PalPatch"

@{par}                              @{fg shine}How to use PalPatch@{fg text}
@{par}
@{par}Either execute PalPatch as a command or at the CLI prompt as follows:
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}PalPatch <path/filename (pattern)>@{fg text}
@{par}
@{par}where @{fg fill}path@{fg text} is the path of the images you wish to change,
@{par}@{fg fill}filename@{fg text} may either be a single file or a pattern.
@{par}
@{par}@{u}For example@{uu}:
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}10.@{bg shine}System3.0:@{bg background}>@{fg text} PalPatch Work:Graphics/Brushes/#?.brush
@{par}
@{par}or
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}10.@{bg shine}Work:Graphics/Brushes:@{bg background}>@{fg text} PalPatch #?.brush
@{par}
@{par}@{b}NOTE@{ub}: The IFF file(s) @{b}MUST@{ub} have the same number of colors as your Workbench.

@ENDNODE

