@NODE "BootShow" "BootShow"
@TOC "Author"

@{par}                               @{fg shine}BootShow V1.0@{fg text}
@{par}
@{par}THE Boot Pic viewer for you. Supports random palettes, timing, fading, and
pattern file loading in the following resolutions:
@{par}
@{par}                     @{u}ECS:  2-32 colors   AGA: 2-256 colors@{uu}
@{par}                          @{fg fill}320x200              320x200
@{par}                          640x200              640x200
@{par}                          320x400              320x400
@{par}                          640x400              640x400
@{par}
@{par}                or any overscan variation of these resolutions.@{fg text}
@{par}
@{par}                               @{fg shine}BootShow V2.0!@{fg text}
@{par}
@{par}Watch out for BootShow V2.0 coming out SOON. V2.0 will support ALL video modes
on ALL Amigas!  Will come with Prefs program and automatic random picture and
palette loader if you register - @{fg shine}Registration is FREE!@{fg text}
@{par}
@{par}BootShow V1.0 may be found in pix/boot on any Aminet site.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "MagicWB1.3" "MagicWB1.3"
@TOC "Author"

@{par}                                  @{fg shine}MagicWB1.3@{fg text}
@{par}
@{par}MagicWB1.3 is a program which changes OS1.3 from 2 bitplanes (4 colors) to 3
bitplanes (8 colors) with the MagicWB palette preset so that you can use
@{"Magic Workbench © by Martin Huttenloher" LINK "MWB"} on your A500 or A1000!
@{par}
@{par}@{u}Other utilitiess included with MagicWB1.3 are:@{uu}
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}Pcheck:@{fg text}       Allows you to verify the current number of bitplanes. You may use
@{par}              this program for any purpose or to confirm wether or not Magic-
@{par}              WB1.3 is installed.
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}IconFix1.3:@{fg text}   A small icon fixing utility which will make your icons look like
@{par}              OS2+ icons.
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}IconUnfix1.3:@{fg text} This utility undoes what IconFix1.3 does.
@{par}
@{par}MagicWB1.3 can be found in pix/icon on any Aminet site.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "CSRen" "CSRen V1.0"
@TOC "Author"
@NEXT "Author"

@{par}                                  @{fg shine}CSRen V1.0@{fg text}
@{par}
@{par}This little util is an animators dream come true. Have you ever wished you
could rename all your frames to something else in a flash?  Then this is the
tool for you!  CSRen will take any prefix, suffix and number of digits and then
rename your files accordingly. That's right, you can even change the number of
digits in the number of the filename.
@{par}
@{par}@{u}For example@{uu}:
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}CSRen pic???.iff whatever?????@{fg text}
@{par}
@{par}This will convert pic000.iff, pic001.iff or anything else that fits the pattern
to whatever00000, whatever00001 and so on. So you may include or omit any or
all of the prefix(es) and suffix(es). And it's FAST!

@ENDNODE

