@NODE "CheckGuide" "CheckGuide by Eddy Carroll"
@NEXT "CheckGuide"
@PREV "CheckGuide"
@TOC "Thanks"

@{par}          @{fg shine}CheckGuide 1.0 -- Checks AmigaGuide files for common errors
@{par}
@{par}             by Eddy Carroll, September 1994. Freely distributable.@{fg text}
@{par}
@{par}Introduction
@{par}
@{par}If you've ever tried creating even a modestly sized AmigaGuide file by hand,
@{par}you'll have discovered that it can be quite difficult to keep track of all the
@{par}various links and cross references. As your help file gets larger, it gets
@{par}increasingly harder to ensure that you have remembered to reference all the
@{par}nodes in the file from at least one place, and haven't left any unresolved
@{par}links.
@{par}
@{par}CheckGuide is a simple utility that can detect several common errors in
@{par}AmigaGuide files. The errors it can detect are:
@{par}
@{par}· Extra plain text between an \@ENDNODE and \@NODE (AmigaGuide won't allow such
@{par}  text to ever be displayed)
@{par}
@{par}· Nodes that are defined but not referenced from any other node. Unless your
@{par}  program directly instructs AmigaGuide to access such nodes, the user won't
@{par}  easily be able to access them.
@{par}
@{par}· Links to help nodes that aren't defined within the file.
@{par}
@{par}· Open braces with no preceding \@ character (usually a simple typo).
@{par}
@{par}· \@{" Button "} constructs with no LINK command (an easy mistake to make if
@{par}  you're entering a lot of them).
@{par}
@{par}All of these options can be selectively enabled or disabled.
@{par}
@{par}        @{fg shine}CheckGuide was used in the creation of @{b}THIS@{ub} document!@{fg text}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "MWB" "MagicWB is © by Martin Huttenloher"
@NEXT "MWB"
@PREV "MWB"

@{par}                      @{fg shine}MagicWB is © by Martin Huttenloher@{fg text}
@{par}
@{par}
@{par}                               @{b}MagicWB V2.0
@{par}                               ============@{ub}
@{par}
@{par}
@{par}The definitive WB-Enhancer no Amiga can do without. MagicWB is a full
replacement for the graphic user interface of the Workbench and has become
the standard on the Amiga.
@{par}
@{par}MagicWB 2.0 is completely restructured on a new color-allocation scheme which
more than doubles the speed of the WB and reduces chip-consumption to only a
third compared with all previous versions and also features a highly improved
color palette. MWB 2.0 introduces a never-before-seen standard for over four
dozen of new image-drawers to achieve a more diversified look on your WB.
More icons, dock-brushes, a dozen of new patterns, fonts and a AA-support
complete this special product.
@{par}
@{par}To get the 'real' look and feel of MagicWB, you should make sure that...
@{par}
@{par} · ...you have set the MagicWB-Palette. Do this by clicking on the 'ClickFor
@{par}      Colors' icon.
@{par}
@{par} · ...you have set the resolution of your Workbench to a aspect ratio near 3:4
@{par}      like 640x480, 800x600 or 1024x768.
@{par}
@{par} The demo-version can be found on Aminet biz/demo/MagicWB20d.lha.
@{par}
@{par} @{b}MagicWB is © by Martin Huttenloher.@{ub}

@ENDNODE
